22 Feb 2026 (r6933)

 * Can write object and object patterns with no object type,
   like {() }, as god intended.

 * Approximatley 6x speedup to the optimization phase.

16 Feb 2026 (r6926)

 * Footnotes and floating figures are working well enough that
   you can write a paper if you hand-hold the layout a little.

 * Finally fixed a long-standing deficiency in the boxes-and-glue
   algorithm where the relative expandibility/contractiveness of
   glue was not taken into account during optimization (only for
   intra-line spacing). This was why hfill() didn't do what you wanted.

9 Feb 2026 (r6920)

 * Rewrite of the core layout routines to support floating elements
   and (in the future) irregular, non-rectangular columns. Still
   needs a lot of work to make it look nice, though.

26 Jan 2026 (r6905)

 * Add basic SVG support. Only supports the PDF backend. Image
   dimensions become floats.

 * Fixed a problem where font metrics were about 0.8% off. Improved
   compliance of output PDFs.

 * Began splitting up the messy layout.bovex into individual
   libraries in order to try to get that code tractable again.

26 Oct 2025

 * Fixed a problem with the pdf generation code that would drop
   all non-ascii codepoints for built-in fonts. We can't have full
   Unicode support for these fonts (only WinAnsi), so I still
   recommend against them.

21 Sep 2025

 * Now bundling my modified llama with the source code so that you
   can compile the LLM stuff without imagining what changes I made.

 * Fixed bug with type-annotated expressions always being considered
   valuable for generalization.

 * Fixed type of vec-update primop.

 * Fixed another bug with vector type.

 * Fixed bug where nullary constructors that were shadowed by function
   declarations would not be rewritten properly.

30 Mar 2025

 * Now when using layout.bovex, you can write \\ for a line break,
   which behaves just like a paragraph without a big gap after.
   This is much nicer.

 * Add float-to-string (%.17g) primop.

 * Improve error messages.

15 Mar 2025 (r6376)

 * Add trunc primop.

 * Improve error messages.

14 Mar 2025 (r6371)

 * When embedding a transparent image in a PDF, composite it on
   white instead of just ignoring the alpha channel.

 * Unicode TrueType fonts are working now! There may still be a few
   minor problems.

 * Document metadata is not limited to 64 characters any more, and
   handles encoding a little bit better.

7 Mar 2025 (r6348)

 * More compatibility improvements for generated PDFs (e.g. Acrobat
   should no longer warn about "invalid BBox"). Unicode TrueType fonts
   are almost supported (display looks good; copy/paste is garbage).

6 Mar 2025 (r6347)

 * Generated PDFs now include width tables for built-in fonts, which
   should increase compatibility. Some other minor bugfixes in PDF
   export code.

20 Feb 2025 (r6304)

 * Primops that load files (notably font-load-file) now search include
   paths (including by default the BoVeX program directory), which is
   what you always wanted. This makes it easier to run bovex from
   another directory, like if you write another SIGBOVIK paper using
   it.

21 Jun 2024 (r5931)

 * Fixed the bug with mutually-recursive functions that have polymorphic
   variables in their environment (and use them at multiple different
   types). This may inhibit some optimizations but otherwise should
   work correctly now.

19 Jun 2024 (r5927)

 * PDF files written by BoVeX now use flate compression, which saves a
   lot of bytes (particularly for embedded TTFs).

9 Jun 2024 (r5906)

 * Did long-standing TODO. Now dynamically-constructed nodes are always
   in normal form, because adjacent text nodes are concatenated when
   the nodes are built. Fixes some incorrect spacing (e.g. after comments)
   in documents.

8 Jun 2024 (r5905)

 * Fixed bugs in the PDF export code. Renders correctly in Firefox now.

 * Added changelog.

6 Jun 2024 (r5903)

 * This was when I uploaded the final video and the first version of the
   webpage at http://tom7.org/bovex/.
